		<p style="display: none;"><input type="hidden" id="poll_42_nonce" name="wp-polls-nonce" value="b349908fae" /></p>
		<p style="display: none;"><input type="hidden" name="poll_id" value="42" /></p>
		<h4>What is your opinion as to the web designers role in mobile design? <a href="http://css-tricks.com/repoll-whos-responsibility-is-mobile-design/">#</a></h4>

<div id="polls-42-ans" class="wp-polls-ans">

<ul class="wp-polls-ul group">
		<li class="group"><input type="radio" id="poll-answer-247" name="poll_42" value="247" /> <label for="poll-answer-247">It is <strong>my job</strong> to make sure the website looks and functions well on mobile devices.</label></li>
		<li class="group"><input type="radio" id="poll-answer-248" name="poll_42" value="248" /> <label for="poll-answer-248">It is <strong>the mobile device's job</strong> to make sure my website looks and functions well.</label></li>
		</ul>

